	Lohans gun art    
	 Los Angeles, April 29 (Reuters): Lindsay Lohan today defended as art a photo of herself holding a gun to her mouth that sparked alarm about the former A-list actress whose life and career have spiralled downward in recent years.      
	Lohan, 23, said the photo that she posted on Twitter was from a shoot for a book about the dark side of glamour by celebrity photographer Tyler Shields. Its not softcore porn hunny, its called ART, the Mean Girls actress said on Twitter, responding to criticism on the micro-blogging website.    
	Pam crush    
	London (PTI): Actress and model Pamela Anderson has a massive crush on President Obama and thinks he is incredibly sexy. Anderson is one of the favourite contestants on American reality show Dancing With The Stars and has a unique wish in case she wins the title. She wants to rush to Washington and do the fandango with Obama, reports the Daily Star.    
	Alba dinner    
	London (PTI): Actress Jessica Alba chose a quiet dinner with husband Cash Warren at a small restaurant over a champagne-fuelled party to celebrate her 29th birthday. The couple, who have a 22-month-old daughter, Honor Marie Warren, ate at a small diner in New York, reports the Daily Mail. Albas birthday outfit consisted of a short party dress with three coloured segments  the top in gold, the middle in navy blue and the bottom green.     
	Posh fan    
	London (PTI): Pop star Beyonce Knowles wants Victoria Beckham to design her tour outfits. The singer is a huge admirer of the former Spice Girl-turned-fashion designers collections and is keen that she creats some outfits for her concerts. Beyonce is a big fan of Victorias work who was hugely flattered and has agreed to suggest some designs, a source said.                                                                                                                                                       
